<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Tate &amp; Lyle Pounds 7m purchase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Tate &amp; Lyle, the sugar and sweeteners group, has paid Pounds 7.2m for
Hartham Holdings, a feed and fertiliser business owned by Cultor of Finland.
Hartham comprises FSL Bells, a farm feed supplement business, and Soil
Fertility Dunns, a specialist fertiliser company.
</TEXT>
