FT  15 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Calderburn 25% lower at Pounds 2.1m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Calderburn, the Preston-based office furniture group, returned pre-tax
profits of Pounds 2.1m for 1993, a 25 per cent shortfall on the previous
year's Pounds 2.83m.
The 1993 figure took account of non-recurring costs of Pounds 400,000, but
excluded any contribution from Specialised Banking Furniture International,
acquired on December 29.
Turnover improved from Pounds 25.9m to Pounds 26.7m. Earnings emerged at
