<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Hartstone to raise at least Pounds 15m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Hartstone, the hosiery and handbags group, yesterday announced details of a
rescue refinancing including an equity issue to raise more than Pounds 15m
this summer.
Hartstone is required to repay Pounds 15m by October to its creditors as a
condition of the new financing arrangements. These will provide lending
facilities until January 15 1996. The group said yesterday it intended to
issue shares to raise the funds, and to provide any necessary working
capital.
The new financing arrangements include:
As part of July 1993's standstill arrangements, the banks made extra
facilities available. The remaining Pounds 8.3m of this is to be repaid with
about Pounds 3.3m of the amount owed at the beginning of the standstill
period. The banks have converted the balance of their lending - about Pounds
45.1m - into secured loans.
The holders of the notes issued by Hartstone Holdings, the US holding
company, have agreed to continue to lend about Dollars 47.1m (Pounds 31.6m)
of their original total loans of Dollars 50m, the balance of which is to be
repaid. Of the continuing loans, a further Dollars 2.1m will be repaid on
March 31.
Charterhouse Group International will be paid about Dollars 900,000 in
partial payment of the outstanding consideration for Etienne Aigner and
Michael Stevens. The balance is to be converted into a secured term loan of
about Dollars 11.9m of which Dollars 600,000 will be repaid on March 31.
Aggregate interest to March 31 - about Pounds 5.6m - to the main creditors
is to be paid.
</TEXT>
