<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAR 94 / Observer: Welkom
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Parents of students at that seat of learning, the University of Leicester,
are invited to a rare Open Day next Saturday, March 19, when there will be
an opportunity to observe the redbrick institution in action. 'Their is a
wide range of demonstartions, talks and displays envolving the whole
University,' says the invitation, presumably in an attempt to spell it out.
The English Faculty, clearly, should be the first stop for concerned mums
and dads.
</TEXT>
