FT  15 MAR 94 / Ruling in Tupe test case
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sixty-three employees who lost their jobs when IBM in Portsmouth changed its
contract caterer could receive up to Pounds 500,000 in compensation in a
further important test case for the Transfer of Undertakings (Protection of
Employment) regulations.
Southampton industrial tribunal has ruled that the Tupe regulations, which
give workers some protection in business transfers, did apply to the
transfer. Bromwich Catering, which won the contract from Gardner Merchant
argued - along with IBM - that the regulations did not apply. The result
could have implications for forthcoming Tupe catering cases.
