<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAR 94 / New Zealand balances books
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY HALL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The New Zealand government expects to balance its books in the financial
year to March 31, Minister of Finance Bill Birch said yesterday, writes
Terry Hall from Wellington.
Last October, the government forecast a deficit of NZDollars 1.8bn (Pounds
686m) this year, and balance by 1996. However, tax revenues were running
NZDollars 800m higher than expected, Mr Birch said, while government
spending was NZDollars 500m less than forecast. He predicted a surplus of
NZDollars 300m next year.
