<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAR 94 / Asylum seeker detainee collapses
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EDWARD MORTIMER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A detainee at the Home Office centre at which almost all 200 inmates are on
hunger strike collapsed yesterday, the Home Office said last night, Edward
Mortimer writes.
It said that seven had been separated from the other detainees at the
Campsfield centre for asylum seekers, near Oxford. 'They are supervised by a
nurse and checked every half hour,' the Home Office said.
It denied allegations from other detainees that some had been force-fed by
Home Office officials and staff of Group 4 security company, which runs the
centre.
The Home Office added that the detainee who had collapsed had been seen by a
doctor who was 'not concerned about his medical condition'.
</TEXT>
<XX>
