FT  14 MAR 94 / Asda raises stakes in price war
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT CORZINE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Asda has signalled that it intends to sharpen its strategic focus on pricing
in a move which will add to competitive pressures in the UK grocery market,
Robert Corzine writes.
It wants to reduce one-off, promotional price cuts in favour of everyday low
pricing. Such a policy puts pressure on suppliers to reduce their prices.
This is the latest development in a steady drive to prepare for saturation
in the industry by focusing on low prices and removing as many costs as
possible.
