FT  14 MAR 94 / Defence chief quits as affair is alleged
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT CORZINE and PHILIP STEPHENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Air Marshal Sir Peter Harding, chief of the Defence Staff, resigned last
night after a newspaper alleged that he was having an affair with the former
wife of a retired Conservative politician, Robert Corzine and Philip
Stephens write.
A Ministry of Defence statement said that Sir Peter had tendered his
resignation with immediate effect and that Mr Malcolm Rifkind, the defence
secretary, had accepted it.
The News of the World alleged there had been an affair between Sir Peter and
Lady Bienvenida Buck, ex-wife of Sir Anthony Buck, a former navy minister.
Their marriage broke up last year.
Sir Peter Inge, the army chief of staff and the most senior of the three
service chiefs, becomes temporary chief of the Defence Staff. He will stay
in the post until a permanent successor is appointed by Mr John Major, the
prime minister.
The resignation, which came within hours of the revelations about Sir
Peter's private life, was in line with the much tougher line on personal
conduct ordered by Mr Major after a spate of ministerial scandals earlier
this year.
